<subSubSection id="6CBDD680FF3983C8FCF85E75FE93FDF6" lastPageId="133" lastPageNumber="133" pageId="132" pageNumber="132" type="description">
<paragraph id="2418850BFF3983C9FCF85E75FCCFF997" blockId="132.[800,1453,1556,1933]" pageId="132" pageNumber="132">
<emphasis id="16D35919FF3983C9FCF85E75FCEBF9D7" box="[828,891,1557,1580]" italics="true" pageId="132" pageNumber="132">Notes.</emphasis>
– 
<materialsCitation id="94CF8F56FF3983C9FC515E75FC64F9B7" collectionCode="A" pageId="132" pageNumber="132" specimenCount="1">
<collectionCode id="42B61DCEFF3983C9FC515E75FC39F9D6" box="[917,937,1557,1581]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15406" name="Harvard University - Arnold Arboretum" pageId="132" pageNumber="132" type="Herbarium">A</collectionCode>
genus of three Eurasian species, and the generic 
<typeStatus id="FB1C3BA9FF3983C9FCE55E55FCC1F9B6" box="[801,849,1589,1613]" pageId="132" pageNumber="132">type</typeStatus>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E3A7FE88FF3983C9FC9E5E54FC64F9B7" box="[858,1012,1588,1612]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Thlaspi" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="132" pageNumber="132" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arvense">
<emphasis id="16D35919FF3983C9FC9E5E54FC64F9B7" box="[858,1012,1588,1612]" italics="true" pageId="132" pageNumber="132">Thlaspi arvense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</materialsCitation>
L., is a cosmopolitan weed and cultivated plant.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2418850BFF3983C9FCF85E15FB83F8D6" blockId="132.[800,1453,1556,1933]" pageId="132" pageNumber="132">
As recognized by 
<bibRefCitation id="4036F8FAFF3983C9FBCA5E15FB4DF976" author="CANDOLLE, A. - P. DE" box="[1038,1245,1653,1677]" pageId="132" pageNumber="132" pagination="169 - 252" refId="ref136851" refString="CANDOLLE, A. - P. DE (1821 a). Memoire sur la famille des Cruciferes. Mem. Mus. Hist. Nat. 7: 169 - 252." type="journal article" year="1821">
CANDOLLE (1821 
<bibRefCitation id="4036F8FAFF3983C9FB155E15FB4DF976" author="CANDOLLE, A. - P. DE" box="[1233,1245,1653,1677]" pageId="132" pageNumber="132" refId="ref136885" refString="CANDOLLE, A. - P. DE (1821 b). Regni vegetabilis systema naturale 2. Paris." type="book" year="1821">a</bibRefCitation>
</bibRefCitation>
, 1821b), 
<bibRefCitation id="4036F8FAFF3983C9FA805E15FCFEF957" author="BOISSIER, E." pageId="132" pageNumber="132" pagination="139 - 409" refId="ref136317" refString="BOISSIER, E. (1867 a). Cruciferae. Fl. Orient. 1: 139 - 409." type="journal article" year="1867">BOISSIER (1867a)</bibRefCitation>
, and subsequent authors prior to 1973, 
<taxonomicName id="E3A7FE88FF3983C9FAD15EF4FACEF957" box="[1301,1374,1684,1708]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Thlaspi" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="132" pageNumber="132" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="16D35919FF3983C9FAD15EF4FACEF957" box="[1301,1374,1684,1708]" italics="true" pageId="132" pageNumber="132">Thlaspi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was so broadly delimited to include over 100 species. 
<bibRefCitation id="4036F8FAFF3983C9FADC5ED5FA38F936" author="MEYER, F. K." box="[1304,1448,1717,1741]" pageId="132" pageNumber="132" pagination="449 - 470" refId="ref141119" refString="MEYER, F. K. (1973). Conspectus der &quot; Thlaspi &quot; - Arten Europas, Afrikas und Vorderasiens. Feddes Repert. 84: 449 - 470." type="journal article" year="1973">MEYER (1973</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="4036F8FAFF3983C9FCE65EB5FCC4F916" author="MEYER, F. K." box="[802,852,1749,1773]" pageId="132" pageNumber="132" pagination="129 - 154" refId="ref141151" refString="MEYER, F. K. (1979). Kritische Revision der &quot; Thlaspi &quot; - Arten Europas, Afrikas und Vorderasiens. I. Geschichte, Morphologie und Chorologie. Feddes Repert. 90: 129 - 154." type="journal article" year="1979">1979</bibRefCitation>
) retained only six species in the genus and transferred the remaining taxa into a dozen segregates based primarily on seed-coat anatomy.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2418850BFF3983C8FCF85F55FEF6FE76" blockId="132.[800,1453,1556,1933]" lastBlockId="133.[136,788,277,525]" lastPageId="133" lastPageNumber="133" pageId="132" pageNumber="132">
However, subsequent authors (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="4036F8FAFF3983C9FB7A5F55FA37F8B7" author="GREUTER, W. &amp; H. M. BURDET &amp; G. LONG" box="[1214,1447,1844,1869]" pageId="132" pageNumber="132" refId="ref139316" refString="GREUTER, W., H. M. BURDET &amp; G. LONG (1986). Med-checklist, a critical inventory of vascular plants of the circum-mediterranaean countries 3." type="journal volume" year="1986">GREUTER et al., 1986</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="4036F8FAFF3983C9FCE65F35FBCAF896" author="APPEL, O. &amp; I. A. AL-SHEHBAZ" box="[802,1114,1877,1901]" pageId="132" pageNumber="132" pagination="75 - 174" refId="ref135717" refString="APPEL, O. &amp; I. A. AL-SHEHBAZ (2003). Cruciferae. In: KUBITZKI, K. &amp; C. BAYER (ed.), The families and genera of vascular plants 5: 75 - 174." type="journal article" year="2003">APPEL &amp; AL-SHEHBAZ, 2003</bibRefCitation>
) retained the genus in the broad sense, whereas others (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="4036F8FAFF3983C9FBFE5F15FA97F876" author="AL-SHEHBAZ, I. A." box="[1082,1287,1909,1933]" pageId="132" pageNumber="132" pagination="931 - 954" refId="ref134976" refString="AL-SHEHBAZ, I. A. (2012). A generic and tribal synopsis of the Brassicaceae (Cruciferae). Taxon 61: 931 - 954." type="journal article" year="2012">AL-SHEHBAZ, 2012</bibRefCitation>
, 2014) relied on the available molecular data and placed all except six species in 
<taxonomicName id="E3A7FE88FF3883C8FF625956FF68FEB6" box="[166,248,310,333]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Noccaea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="133" pageNumber="133" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="16D35919FF3883C8FF625956FF68FEB6" box="[166,248,310,333]" italics="true" pageId="133" pageNumber="133">Noccaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of the tribe 
<taxonomicName id="E3A7FE88FF3883C8FE425955FDB0FEB6" box="[390,544,309,333]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="133" pageNumber="133" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Coluteocarpeae">
<emphasis id="16D35919FF3883C8FE425955FDB0FEB6" box="[390,544,309,333]" italics="true" pageId="133" pageNumber="133">Coluteocarpeae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The latter genus also currently encompasses almost all taxa described in 
<taxonomicName id="E3A7FE88FF3883C8FD775935FC84FE96" box="[691,788,341,365]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Iberidella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="133" pageNumber="133" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="16D35919FF3883C8FD775935FC84FE96" box="[691,788,341,365]" italics="true" pageId="133" pageNumber="133">Iberidella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="4036F8FAFF3883C8FF6C5915FEF2FE76" author="BOISSIER, E." box="[168,354,373,397]" pageId="133" pageNumber="133" pagination="378 - 382" refId="ref136038" refString="BOISSIER, E. (1841 b). Novarum generum cruciferarum diagnosis, ex plantarum Aucherianum enumeratione excerpta. Ann. Sci. Nat., Bot. ser. 2, 16: 378 - 382." type="journal article" year="1841">BOISSIER (1841b)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2418850BFF3883C8FF6759F6FE93FDF6" blockId="133.[136,788,277,525]" pageId="133" pageNumber="133">
As recently delimited, 
<bibRefCitation id="4036F8FAFF3883C8FE5559F5FD08FE56" author="ESMAILBEGI, S., I. &amp; AL-SHEHBAZ, M. &amp; POUCH, T. &amp; MANDAKOVA, K. &amp; MUMMENHOFF, M. R. &amp; RAHIMINEJAD, M." box="[401,664,405,429]" pageId="133" pageNumber="133" pagination="324 - 340" refId="ref138418" refString="ESMAILBEGI, S., I. A. AL-SHEHBAZ, M. POUCH, T. MANDAKOVA, K. MUMMENHOFF, M. R. RAHIMINEJAD, M. MIRTADZADINI &amp; M. A. LYSAK (2018). Phylogeny and systematics of the tribe Thlaspideae (Brassicaceae) and the recognition of two new genera. Taxon 67: 324 - 340." type="journal article" year="2018">ESMAILBEGI et al. (2018)</bibRefCitation>
recognized only four species in 
<emphasis id="16D35919FF3883C8FEA459D5FE3FFE36" box="[352,431,437,461]" italics="true" pageId="133" pageNumber="133">
<taxonomicName id="E3A7FE88FF3883C8FEA459D5FE3BFE36" box="[352,427,437,461]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Thlaspi" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="133" pageNumber="133" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Thlaspi</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
of which 
<taxonomicName id="E3A7FE88FF3883C8FDDF59D6FC83FE35" authority="F. K. Mey." authorityName="F. K. Mey." box="[539,787,437,462]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Thlaspi" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="133" pageNumber="133" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kochianum">
<emphasis id="16D35919FF3883C8FDDF59D6FD33FE36" box="[539,675,437,461]" italics="true" pageId="133" pageNumber="133">T. kochianum</emphasis>
F.K. Mey.
</taxonomicName>
was subsequently reduced by GERMAN (2018) to the following species.
</paragraph>
